  "body": "# Problem\r\nProvide user's invited to Status a more direct way to download and install Status as well as find friends.\r\n\r\nWe've revamped the 'web2' user profile page https://join.status.im/user/0x04f1ab965a3db6433923ceba0488ff605f230aca4c4c93bb6563c10b700cfdbbed2a364c980b9cf9679f352584d4da44cc01fc1e7257f1d2b80ffff5af64aa129f\r\n\r\nThis page is already being linked to from: `Profile`  >`Share button`\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n- Url from `Chat` > `Invite friends` button must include full url (i.e. including join.status.im)\r\n- Url from `+ - button` > `Invite friends` must include full url (i.e. including join.status.im)\r\n- QR code of profile share must include full url (i.e. including join.status.im)\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Invite friends links to https://join.status.im/user/\r\n- In case of ENS https://join.status.im/user/<ens name>\r\n- In case of random name https://join.status.im/user/<chat key>\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n- Fix QR code reading ENS https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/10017\r\n- Tweak page styling https://github.com/status-im/universal-links-handler/issues/23\r\n- Investigate compressing Chat key to reduce QR code size\r\n",
